1
00:00:22,273 --> 00:00:25,109
- All quiet today?
- Keeping it like that, boss.

2
00:00:26,944 --> 00:00:29,030
We rule where we stand.

3
00:00:34,202 --> 00:00:37,455
Police sitting on all
corners over these parts.

4
00:00:37,705 --> 00:00:41,834
- Likely because we been dropping bodies.
- Yeah, they do like that.

5
00:00:41,918 --> 00:00:44,587
But some other nigger'll
stop a bullet somewhere else

6
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:46,964
and then they'll stand on the new spot.

7
00:00:47,048 --> 00:00:48,966
Boy marlo closed up shop.

8
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:52,887
Word is, he wholesaling
his packages for now.

9
00:00:54,013 --> 00:00:57,600
He don't got no crews out here at all?
How about his Avenue corners?

10
00:00:59,143 --> 00:01:01,145
Nigger give up quick, didn't he?

11
00:01:01,812 --> 00:01:05,149
I was just beginning to respect
the little motherfucker for showing heart.

12
00:01:06,484 --> 00:01:10,238
Listen. When them police roll out,
step in there and take my corners.

13
00:01:10,321 --> 00:01:11,656
I'm on it, b.

14
00:01:12,782 --> 00:01:16,285
- Cheese steaks from bill's.
- Nah, I did that Tuesday, man.

15
00:01:16,744 --> 00:01:18,371
Fuck it then, you pick.

16
00:01:28,881 --> 00:01:31,509
- No, fuck me.
- What?

17
00:01:32,176 --> 00:01:34,595
- Mope in the truck.
- What about him?

18
00:01:34,679 --> 00:01:36,347
Think I locked him up.

19
00:01:36,722 --> 00:01:38,849
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Avon what's-his-face?

20
00:01:38,975 --> 00:01:40,977
Big player from the projects.

21
00:01:41,143 --> 00:01:43,729
He was the target on that detail
I worked a couple of years back,

22
00:01:43,854 --> 00:01:45,022
the one I told you about.

23
00:01:50,194 --> 00:01:53,531
- Motherfucker's out already.
- Why, what'd he pull?

24
00:01:53,906 --> 00:01:56,200
Six, eight years.
Who the fuck can remember?

25
00:01:56,701 --> 00:01:58,286
And he's out in two?

26
00:01:59,787 --> 00:02:01,372
Maybe I got the years wrong.

27
00:02:02,415 --> 00:02:04,959
Point is, guy's an asshole.
Locked him up, is all.

28
00:02:07,378 --> 00:02:10,840
- Pit b from the market.
- See, now you're thinking like police.

29
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:21,851
When you walk through the garden

30
00:02:22,727 --> 00:02:24,895
you gotta watch your back

31
00:02:26,731 --> 00:02:29,233
well, I beg your pardon

32
00:02:30,318 --> 00:02:32,278
walk the straight and narrow track

33
00:02:32,403 --> 00:02:33,988
walk the straight
and narrow track

34
00:02:34,071 --> 00:02:36,449
if you walk with Jesus

35
00:02:37,908 --> 00:02:40,202
he's gonna save your soul

36
00:02:41,704 --> 00:02:45,207
you gotta keep the devil

37
00:02:45,416 --> 00:02:47,835
way down in the hole

38
00:02:49,253 --> 00:02:51,672
he got fire and the fury

39
00:02:51,756 --> 00:02:53,424
fire and fury

40
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:56,010
at his command

41
00:02:57,219 --> 00:03:00,306
well, you don't have to worry

42
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:04,060
hold on to Jesus' hands

43
00:03:04,352 --> 00:03:07,188
oh, we'll be safe from Satan

44
00:03:08,064 --> 00:03:10,358
when the thunder rolls

45
00:03:11,901 --> 00:03:14,779
you gotta keep the devil

46
00:03:15,821 --> 00:03:19,533
way down in the hole

47
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:30,127
You gotta keep the devil

48
00:03:31,045 --> 00:03:33,214
way down in the hole

49
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,552
way down

50
00:03:38,636 --> 00:03:40,721
way down in the hole

51
00:03:48,521 --> 00:03:50,523
Change in plan.

52
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,484
Bell, you recognize.

53
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:57,279
Second target is a marlo Stanfield,

54
00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:00,157
who's warring with bell
for the West Side corners.

55
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:03,869
- What about kintel Williamson?
- That case is on hold for now.

56
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:08,457
On hold? We just managed to ID
the cellphones on two of his people.

57
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:11,001
- Be that as it may...
- Why not take a few more weeks

58
00:04:11,085 --> 00:04:13,087
so we can put together
what we got on kintel?

59
00:04:13,546 --> 00:04:16,674
We send the case to grand jury
and then start this West Side case.

60
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:19,444
- Othennise, we wasted more than...
- Change of target comes to us

61
00:04:19,468 --> 00:04:21,637
from the commissioner and the deputy ops.

62
00:04:21,971 --> 00:04:25,808
The department is trying to get the
murder rate down by any means necessary.

63
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,477
Kintel was dropping bodies two months ago.

64
00:04:28,561 --> 00:04:31,772
Today, it's the West Side
that's got the bosses spinning.

65
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,109
I know y'all thought it was nothing
for me to sit on that roof

66
00:04:35,359 --> 00:04:38,946
day after 90-degree day,
dodging swarms of cicadas and shit

67
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:40,906
but, damn, this is fucked up!

68
00:04:41,031 --> 00:04:45,244
And all the assets work I did on kintel,
his cars, his cash flow...

69
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,205
Just put that in a drawer?

70
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:58,966
Someday, I wanna work
for a real police department.

71
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,886
Just to see how the fuck they do it.

72
00:05:06,307 --> 00:05:07,558
Mcnulty.

73
00:05:08,559 --> 00:05:09,852
In my office.

74
00:05:17,902 --> 00:05:20,112
- Prez, can you run something out for me?
- What?

75
00:05:20,738 --> 00:05:24,950
I need to know who rented this room in
the downtown Hilton, Thursday before last.

76
00:05:25,117 --> 00:05:26,911
Who rented the room?

77
00:05:27,077 --> 00:05:29,246
Address, credit card details,
whatever you can pull.

78
00:05:30,414 --> 00:05:34,335
- How's it fit with the case?
- It's hard to sayjust yet.

79
00:05:37,588 --> 00:05:40,090
Hey, my man. I'm done mowing.

80
00:05:42,343 --> 00:05:45,679
I figured I'd use this to edge
the weeds around the fence.

81
00:05:46,222 --> 00:05:49,225
- It's gas-powered.
- Means I gotta prime it.

82
00:05:49,391 --> 00:05:51,268
You ain't gotta school me but once.

83
00:05:51,769 --> 00:05:53,479
Get some water before you go back.

84
00:05:53,562 --> 00:05:54,730
All right.

85
00:05:56,732 --> 00:05:58,526
You been going hard at it.

86
00:05:58,609 --> 00:06:00,903
You keep showing up,
I'll keep putting you on.

87
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:03,781
Good, 'cause I ain't got nothing else.

88
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:07,117
You walked back through them old doors,
didn't you?

89
00:06:09,203 --> 00:06:12,623
- Tried to.
- Yeah. I had took you for gone.

90
00:06:13,624 --> 00:06:18,128
Man, parole officers, employment agencies.

91
00:06:18,963 --> 00:06:22,049
Shit, I just felt like I was an
interruption to their lunch break.

92
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:23,884
No family?

93
00:06:25,427 --> 00:06:28,973
None besides my grandmother.
She put me up in her basement.

94
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,850
That's plenty to ask of
the old girl right there.

95
00:06:32,643 --> 00:06:35,145
You could use somebody to talk to
besides your grandmoms.

96
00:06:35,813 --> 00:06:37,356
What about them social worker types?

97
00:06:37,815 --> 00:06:40,526
I hooked up with one dude. He was cool.

98
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:45,489
- But I wasn't ready.
- You look like you're ready now.

99
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:48,923
I mean, you found an ear to bend,
you wouldn't have to talk to me.

100
00:06:49,368 --> 00:06:52,454
Shit, I know you gonna get tired
of looking at my ugly-ass grill.

101
00:06:54,832 --> 00:06:56,542
Drink that too fast, you'll cramp up.

102
00:07:02,423 --> 00:07:04,008
- You're asking?
- I am.

103
00:07:05,175 --> 00:07:06,176
Lieutenant, I didn't...

104
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:09,805
Because I got no problem changing targets
if that's what the bosses tell me to do.

105
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:13,684
Unless it's personal,
like when kima got shot,

106
00:07:14,518 --> 00:07:16,358
I don't care
where we spend our time and money.

107
00:07:16,854 --> 00:07:19,940
Bell, Williamson, whoever.
It's all just police work to me.

108
00:07:20,482 --> 00:07:24,528
I understand that people above my pay grade
have the right to make decisions.

109
00:07:24,653 --> 00:07:26,447
- And if they're wrong?
- They're wrong.

110
00:07:26,530 --> 00:07:28,073
And time will tell, won't it?

111
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:31,285
Now, I'm asking you for the truth.

112
00:07:32,286 --> 00:07:34,288
You went to Colvin behind my back.

113
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:36,498
I'd have gone to the devil himself.

114
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:39,793
Which way you were standing
had nothing to do with it.

115
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:41,795
You piece of shit.

116
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,174
I did it 'cause it had to be done.

117
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:48,802
Just like it had to be done two years ago
when we were first detailed.

118
00:07:49,386 --> 00:07:52,014
Stringer was the target then,
he's still the target now.

119
00:07:56,727 --> 00:08:00,564
Lieutenant, you know, as bosses go,
you're better than most,

120
00:08:01,732 --> 00:08:04,234
and I know you went out of your way
to get me off that boat.

121
00:08:05,486 --> 00:08:08,989
I know that,
but now we're back on the right man.

122
00:08:25,172 --> 00:08:26,423
Detective mcnulty.

123
00:08:28,342 --> 00:08:32,096
When the cuffs go on stringer,
you need to find a new home.

124
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:35,724
You're done in this unit.

125
00:08:47,653 --> 00:08:48,654
Your count, right?

126
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:50,537
Yeah, went almost to
Richmond for this batch.

127
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:52,741
Yeah, I'm holding.

128
00:08:53,617 --> 00:08:55,619
- You did like we say, right?
- Yeah.

129
00:08:55,703 --> 00:08:57,204
Give him that.

130
00:08:58,622 --> 00:09:00,708
We're gonna need another 60 more.

131
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:02,626
- 60 more?
- You know how we do.

132
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:03,961
So don't be crying, Bernard.

133
00:09:13,679 --> 00:09:15,889
- You must have left something out.
- No.

134
00:09:15,973 --> 00:09:18,183
I got the part ones from every sector,
every post.

135
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:21,645
- We're down about 2%.
- No, where exactly are we down?

136
00:09:21,729 --> 00:09:23,814
Larcenies and burglaries are steady.

137
00:09:23,939 --> 00:09:25,899
But shootings and agg assaults are down.

138
00:09:25,983 --> 00:09:29,069
Drug arrests too,
but I guess that won't look so good.

139
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:32,948
I mean, where geographically are we down,
in the district?

140
00:09:33,115 --> 00:09:37,119
Well, the posts near the designated
drug zones are up, almost all of them.

141
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:40,664
That ain't pretty,
but everywhere else it's down.

142
00:09:41,123 --> 00:09:43,000
In some places as much as 4%.

143
00:09:45,753 --> 00:09:49,798
- Bosses gonna love you.
- It's too soon to take any credit.

144
00:09:50,466 --> 00:09:53,677
This might be, what you call that?
A statistical aberration.

145
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:57,097
You ain't gonna tell them
your experiment might be working?

146
00:09:57,181 --> 00:09:58,766
Not yet, no.

147
00:09:59,892 --> 00:10:01,452
But I'll tell you what we are gonna do.

148
00:10:01,685 --> 00:10:04,188
Starting next week,
I want you to pull one car out of service

149
00:10:04,271 --> 00:10:07,608
in the quiet posts in every sector,
all three shifts.

150
00:10:08,066 --> 00:10:12,029
We're gonna take those nine guys
and double up on the high crime posts.

151
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:16,116
If we handle less of it...

152
00:10:16,408 --> 00:10:18,994
We ought to do better
with the crime we got, right?

153
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:26,710
- Can I get two trac disposable phones?
- They're on special.

154
00:10:27,294 --> 00:10:29,338
- Four for 180.
- Just the two.

155
00:10:39,723 --> 00:10:41,892
The late show out at westview is 8:45.

156
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:44,895
We could make that
if we don't make the whole damn run today.

157
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:47,981
Seems to me one phone
is as good as the next.

158
00:10:48,065 --> 00:10:51,276
Only a fool would drive all over the world
when there ain't no need.

159
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:53,403
Keep on with that shit
and I'll leave you here.

160
00:10:53,487 --> 00:10:57,407
I don't trust no man on the road
by hisself, okay? I'm not stupid.

161
00:11:03,205 --> 00:11:05,541
Stupid-ass fucker. Commissioner!

162
00:11:08,252 --> 00:11:09,586
How goes it?

163
00:11:10,254 --> 00:11:13,340
It went a lot better before the mayor's
cabinet meeting.

164
00:11:13,799 --> 00:11:15,175
He rip you?

165
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:19,096
Says we need to finish under 300
for this year, regardless of how.

166
00:11:19,471 --> 00:11:21,765
- Now, I tried to tell...
- Erv, let me ask you.

167
00:11:25,269 --> 00:11:27,509
Where do you guys stand
on this witness assistance thing?

168
00:11:28,188 --> 00:11:29,273
What?

169
00:11:29,523 --> 00:11:31,775
Overhauling the
witness assistance program?

170
00:11:34,111 --> 00:11:37,698
Nobody from the mayor's office called you
regarding witnesses getting killed?

171
00:11:39,283 --> 00:11:41,994
I got a call from chief of staff
a week ago, yeah.

172
00:11:42,077 --> 00:11:45,706
But all he said was I should try not
to have any more witnesses get killed.

173
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:47,749
But overhauling the program?

174
00:11:48,125 --> 00:11:52,087
Unless someone spends more money, there's
not a hell of a lot my people can do.

175
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:54,466
You haven't talked
to the mayor directly on this?

176
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,719
You're not gonna fuck me on this?

177
00:11:58,802 --> 00:12:01,138
As it is, I got the
mayor's teeth in my ass.

178
00:12:01,263 --> 00:12:03,140
Your name does not get mentioned.

179
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:07,936
Mayor didn't say a word to me.

180
00:12:09,688 --> 00:12:10,898
Thanks.

181
00:12:13,525 --> 00:12:17,487
Is nothing.
This is DC's number one, wpgc 95.5.

182
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,334
Where the fuck we at now?

183
00:12:32,002 --> 00:12:35,213
Just buy four or five. Do it like
that and it'll go twice as quick.

184
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:39,176
I want a Shrek slurpee, Bernard,
and some krispy kreme.

185
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:45,724
All this from one disposable cellphone?

186
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:47,684
And a dead one too.

187
00:12:48,727 --> 00:12:52,022
It was used by marlo's people
and picked up off the ground by kima's cl.

188
00:12:52,689 --> 00:12:54,942
Problem is it's just raw data.
We need to firm up

189
00:12:55,025 --> 00:12:58,862
what we know about marlo's operation
with surveillance and ci info.

190
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:00,614
On the other hand...

191
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:04,826
If we had a burner that we knew was used
by one of stringer's players

192
00:13:05,327 --> 00:13:08,997
we could use what we know about
that organization to make connections.

193
00:13:09,539 --> 00:13:12,084
Get us one good phone,
we'll give you the network.

194
00:13:13,168 --> 00:13:15,629
- That's the good news.
- And what's the bad?

195
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:20,050
It's all historical.
We can give you the network no problem,

196
00:13:20,759 --> 00:13:24,429
but by then it's a week old
and they've dumped their phones.

197
00:13:24,513 --> 00:13:28,517
And how we get a wire up on that
I haven't figured out yet.

198
00:13:29,518 --> 00:13:31,436
Well, see that you do, detective.

199
00:13:42,406 --> 00:13:45,617
Yeah, you keep this job,
I'm gonna gain some serious weight.

200
00:13:45,993 --> 00:13:47,536
- Just the two?
- Just the two.

201
00:13:48,036 --> 00:13:49,454
You never heard of buying in bulk?

202
00:13:49,538 --> 00:13:53,375
You could be saving them people money.
Better still, spending it on me.

203
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:13,186
- Why you got a gun, Bernard?
- You ain't heard?

204
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:17,733
- Avon's home, so we tooling up.
- You ain't the only one on parole.

205
00:14:17,816 --> 00:14:21,737
- You riding my last good nerve.
- That ain't the only thing I can ride.

206
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:23,697
Just get me back to the interstate.

207
00:14:24,823 --> 00:14:26,992
Big white bag, got the big white bag.

208
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:32,247
- Which one is he again?
- Broadus, street name of bodie.

209
00:14:32,873 --> 00:14:35,959
He used to be in the low-rises.
Had a tower later on.

210
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:44,092
Big white, got the big white.

211
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:49,097
How many more minutes you think
he's got on that phone?

212
00:14:53,185 --> 00:14:56,646
- Fuck this, let's hit the bar.
- Lester needs a phone, man.

213
00:14:56,938 --> 00:14:59,066
No, there's an easier way.
I'll show you tomorrow.

214
00:15:01,151 --> 00:15:02,402
Come on.

215
00:15:03,737 --> 00:15:05,072
I'm buying.

216
00:15:15,248 --> 00:15:17,667
Big white bag, got the big white bag.

217
00:15:21,505 --> 00:15:23,256
She just wants me to be happy, you know?

218
00:15:24,466 --> 00:15:27,677
And I mean,
I do the same for her when I can.

219
00:15:29,012 --> 00:15:31,014
Like this thing with the police detective.

220
00:15:31,848 --> 00:15:34,184
Brianna says she wants me
to go downtown with her and...

221
00:15:35,477 --> 00:15:37,687
I don't know, hear the man out about Dee.

222
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:41,900
I know there ain't nothing to it
but she is all upset, you know?

223
00:15:42,692 --> 00:15:44,736
I tried to tell her what you told me.

224
00:15:45,403 --> 00:15:49,533
But she say she wanna go down there
and talk to him herself, I guess.

225
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:52,410
- You told her about the cop?
- What?

226
00:15:52,536 --> 00:15:55,163
About the detective.
What you told me, you told her?

227
00:15:55,497 --> 00:15:59,376
It's her son, right? Ain't she got
a right to know what's going on?

228
00:16:02,212 --> 00:16:04,381
- Look, I just thought...
- What?

229
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:09,327
Why the fuck you gonna get her all upset
over some bullshit?

230
00:16:10,095 --> 00:16:12,389
A year later,
everybody forgot about the shit,

231
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:14,224
you go running your mouth about nothing?

232
00:16:14,975 --> 00:16:16,768
- String...
- And she gonna believe that too.

233
00:16:16,852 --> 00:16:19,521
What moms is not gonna believe
her son didn't kill hisself?

234
00:16:20,438 --> 00:16:23,775
She gonna take that
shit, go half-crazy with it.

235
00:16:25,152 --> 00:16:26,528
- I just...
- You just what?

236
00:16:27,737 --> 00:16:29,239
Sorry!

